This paper deals with privacy issues in outsourcing network functionality to the cloud, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of software-defined networks (SDN), which is a topic in distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The privacy concerns addressed in the paper are related to confidential information leakage, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper proposes a practical solution for outsourcing network functionality, which involves obfuscation techniques, a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
